            The mutant version (<ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">C1684T</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">Arg554 → Trp</ENAMEX>; Figure <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">7a</NUMEX>) of
            <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">SDHA</ENAMEX> has a normal <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">K</ENAMEX> 
            <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">m</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">K</ENAMEX> 
            i (for malonate) but is much more
            sensitive to downregulation by oxaloacetate (OAA).
            Mutating the conserved arginine <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">residue</ENAMEX> at position
            <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">554</NUMEX> to a tryptophan causes a loss of a polar residue
